## Context: What We Are Fixing

The platform was built desktop-first. Three areas are broken or severely degraded on
mobile (tested at 390px viewport width, which is iPhone 14/15 standard):

1. **Listings sidebar filter panel** — a wide sidebar with 10+ filter sections
   (price range, year range, total time, deal type, maintenance burden, etc.) renders
   as a collapsed or overflow state on mobile. Users cannot practically filter inventory
   on a phone.

2. **Listing detail page** — the detail page has 6–8 stacked panels (score summary,
   Comp & Cost chart, Engine Value, FAA snapshot, Avionics, Aircraft Details). The comps
   chart in particular likely overflows its container on narrow viewports. The panel
   stacking order on mobile should prioritize the most important information first.

3. **Deal Desk** — the 9-section P&L tool with a 3×3 sensitivity grid is the most
   complex page. The sensitivity grid requires horizontal scrolling on mobile at minimum
   and is functionally unusable without specific treatment.

