## Task 3 — Deal Desk Mobile Treatment

### Goal
The Deal Desk must be usable on mobile for reviewing a deal, even if some advanced
features are desktop-only. The critical path on mobile is: see the aircraft, see P&L
summary, see if it's a good deal. The sensitivity grid is explicitly desktop-only.

### Step 3.1 — Sensitivity grid: desktop-only
In `app/internal/deal-desk/page.tsx`, find the 3×3 sensitivity grid section.
Wrap it with:
```tsx
<div className="hidden md:block">
  {/* sensitivity grid */}
</div>
```
On mobile, replace it with a simple text summary:
```tsx
<div className="block md:hidden rounded-lg border border-border p-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
  <p className="font-medium text-foreground mb-1">Sensitivity Analysis</p>
  <p>Open on desktop to view the full price × cost sensitivity grid.</p>
</div>
```

### Step 3.2 — Section stacking
The Deal Desk 9 sections currently likely render in a multi-column grid on desktop.
On mobile they should all be single-column, full-width stacked sections.
Find any `grid-cols-2` or `grid-cols-3` layouts in the Deal Desk and ensure they have
`grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2` (or similar) so mobile always gets single column.

### Step 3.3 — Input fields
All numeric input fields in the Deal Desk should have `inputMode="numeric"` or
`type="number"` so mobile keyboards show the number pad automatically.
Scan the Deal Desk form inputs and add this attribute where missing.

### Step 3.4 — Sticky summary bar
On mobile, add a sticky bar at the bottom of the viewport that shows the current
deal P&L summary at a glance: Est. Profit / ROI / Deal Grade. This should update
reactively as inputs change.
```tsx
{/* Mobile sticky P&L summary bar */}
<div className="fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 z-40 block md:hidden
                bg-background border-t border-border px-4 py-3
                flex items-center justify-between shadow-lg">
  <div className="text-sm">
    <span className="text-muted-foreground">Est. Profit</span>
    <span className="ml-2 font-semibold text-foreground">{formatCurrency(estProfit)}</span>
  </div>
  <div className="text-sm">
    <span className="text-muted-foreground">ROI</span>
    <span className="ml-2 font-semibold text-foreground">{roiPct}%</span>
  </div>
  <div className="text-sm">
    <span className={`font-bold ${dealGradeColor}`}>{dealGrade}</span>
  </div>
</div>
```

Wire this to the same state already driving the existing P&L summary section. On mobile
also add `pb-20` to the main Deal Desk content container so the sticky bar doesn't
overlap the last section.

