## Task 4 — Global Mobile Header Polish

### Step 4.1 — Header overflow check
In `app/layout.tsx` or the Header component, check that the header doesn't overflow
or create horizontal scroll at 390px. The search bar + nav items + theme toggle should
either fit or collapse gracefully. If the header has items that wrap badly, add a
hamburger / collapse pattern for secondary nav items at mobile width. Keep it simple —
this is not a full nav redesign, just ensuring nothing overflows.

### Step 4.2 — Back navigation on listing detail
On mobile, a "← Back to listings" link at the top of the listing detail page is
standard UX and eliminates needing to use the browser back button. Check if this
already exists. If not, add it:
```tsx
<Link href="/listings" className="block md:hidden text-sm text-muted-foreground
  hover:text-foreground mb-4 flex items-center gap-1">
  ← Back to listings
</Link>
```
Place it just below the header, above the aircraft title.

